@startuml WE1-2-before-dependency-graph
title WE1-2 — File Tab: BEFORE dependency graph

skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor White
    BorderColor Black
}
skinparam arrow {
    Color #444444
}

component "CanvassDesktop\n----\nGod-class (1899 lines)" as CanvassDesktop #OrangeRed
component VolumeCommandController
component VolumeInputController
component HistogramHelper
component VolumeDataSetRenderer

package "External / Native" #FFF2CC {
    component StandaloneFileBrowser
    component FitsReader
}

package "Unity / SteamVR platform" #E1F5FE {
    component UnityEngine
    component "UnityEngine.UI" as UnityEngineUI
    component TMPro
    component "Valve.VR" as ValveVR
}

' Dependencies
CanvassDesktop ..> VolumeCommandController : FindObjectOfType
CanvassDesktop ..> VolumeInputController  : FindObjectOfType
CanvassDesktop ..> HistogramHelper        : FindObjectOfType
CanvassDesktop ..> VolumeDataSetRenderer  : GetComponentsInChildren
CanvassDesktop ..> StandaloneFileBrowser  : static async call
CanvassDesktop ..> FitsReader             : P/Invoke / static call
CanvassDesktop --|> UnityEngine           : extends
CanvassDesktop --> UnityEngineUI          : direct field access
CanvassDesktop --> TMPro                  : direct field access
CanvassDesktop ..> ValveVR               : type usage

caption CanvassDesktop owns all file-tab responsibilities — UI traversal, file picking,\nFITS parsing, and cube loading — with no layer separation.

@enduml
